The paper deals with the complexity of Boolean queries over ordered relational structures, which is a topic in database theory (cs.DB). The use of second-order logic and the investigation of the poly-logarithmic time hierarchy suggest that the paper may also belong to the logic (cs.LO), computational complexity (cs.CC), and data structures (cs.DS) sub-categories. Additionally, the relevance of the logic and complexity class to several problems in database theory suggests that the paper may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
